<FIRST>r a BC-BoyImpaled     07-09 0186</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Boy Impaled,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Boy Dangles From Fence When Spike Goes Through Neck</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY26</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A boy who was impaled by his neck on an iron
spike after he lost his balance and slipped while climbing over a
6-foot-high fence was in serious condition Saturday at a hospital,
officials said.
   The picket went up from under 15-year-old Julio Castillo's neck
and out his mouth, police and fire officials said. Rescue workers
were forced to prop him up with a ladder while they cut a section
from the fence.
   ``The fence had to go with him to the emergency room,'' said Fire
Department Capt. James Rogers, who helped with the rescue.
   Once at the City Hospital Center, Fire Department rescue workers
scrubbed up and worked with the doctors to remove the spike from the
boy's mouth, Rogers said. The spike just missed the boy's jugular
vein.
   The accident occurred about 5:30 p.m. near the boy's apartment
building in the borough of Queens. The boy dangled from the fence
for several minutes before rescue workers arrived. He was conscious
through the ordeal, officials said.
</TEXT>
