<HEAD>Six People Returning From A Family Reunion Killed In Van-Truck Wreck</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS last 2 grafs to CORRECT spelling of Riviera Beach, Fla.;
clarify relationship of two injured women to driver.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WAYCROSS, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A van loaded with 15 people returning from a
family reunion collided with a pickup early Sunday, killing six
people and injuring 10, police said.
   Four of the dead were children, one just 2 weeks old, after the
12:15 a.m. accident on U.S. 84 about 4 miles west of this
southeastern Georgia town.
   U.S. Army Staff Sgt. James Koonce, 29, of Hinesville was driving
the van loaded with relatives following a family reunion in Hahira
when it collided with the truck driving by Scott Steedley, 16, of
Manor, said Jack Crawford, Waycross post commander for the Georgia
State Patrol.
   Crawford said the truck apparently veered off the road and then
back into the path of the van.
   Neither driver was killed. Steedley was listed in extremely
critical condition at Baptist Hospital in Jacksonville, Fla., early
Sunday and Koonce was in fair condition at Ware Memorial Hospital in
Waycross, Crawford said.
   But Koonce's wife, daughter, sister and two nephews were killed,
along with the father of one of the nephews.
   Crawford identified the dead as: wife Shirley Koonce, 28, of
Hinesville; daughter Sheena Marie Koonce, 4, of Hinesville; sister
Valerie Tribble, 10, of Hahira; nephew Lorenzo Barquel Wilson, 1{,
of Riviera Beach, Fla.; 2-week-old nephew Curtaious Johnson of
Riveria Beach; and the infant's father, Cornell Johnson of Riveria
Beach, whose age was not immediately available.
   In addition to the two drivers, Koonce's four sons and another
daughter, two of Mrs. Koonce's sisters and a niece from West Palm
Beach, Fla., were hospitalized. The two women were listed in
critical condition.
